Find { \mathbf a \cdot \mathbf b } 
if \left| {\mathbf a} \right| = 9, \left| {\mathbf b} \right| = 10,
and the angle between {\mathbf a} and {\mathbf b} is 
- \frac{\pi}{3} radians.

Find { \mathbf a \cdot \mathbf b } 
if \left| {\mathbf a} \right| = 1, \left| {\mathbf b} \right| = 3,
and the angle between {\mathbf a} and {\mathbf b} is 
- \frac{\pi}{7} radians.

\bf{a} \times \bf{b}= \bf{i} + 
 \bf{j} + 
 \bf{k}

\mathbf{i} + 
\mathbf{j} +
\mathbf{k}

static.solution:
\vec{OP}=\left\lt 0,2,2\right> and \vec{OQ}=\left\lt 4,0,7\right>. Thus,



S=\frac{1}{2} || \vec{OP} \times \vec{OQ} ||



We compute the cross product:



\vec{OP} \times \vec{OQ}=
\left| \begin{array}{ccc}
 \boldsymbol{i} \amp  \boldsymbol{j} \amp  \boldsymbol{k} \\
 0 \amp  2 \amp  2 \\
 4 \amp  0 \amp  7
\end{array} \right|
= 
  \left| \begin{array}{cc} 2 \amp  2 \\ 0 \amp  7 \end{array} \right| \boldsymbol{i}
- \left| \begin{array}{cc} 0 \amp  2 \\ 4 \amp  7 \end{array} \right| \boldsymbol{j}
+ \left| \begin{array}{cc} 0 \amp  2 \\ 4 \amp  0 \end{array} \right| \boldsymbol{k} 


\qquad = 14 \boldsymbol{i} + 8 \boldsymbol{j}  - 8 \boldsymbol{k}



S=\frac{1}{2}|| 14 \boldsymbol{i} + 8 \boldsymbol{j}  - 8 \boldsymbol{k} ||
   =\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{(14)^2+(8)^2+(-8)^2}
   \approx 9.

